The paper focuses on developing a model for software team composition, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The study also involves the use of personality types and gender variables, which are related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The techniques used for model development, such as logistic regression and decision tree, are related to machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The study also involves the use of rough sets theory, which is related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
